  user_input {
    user_response: "# SYSTEM DIRECTIVE: $10,000 AWWWARDS-LEVEL UI/UX ENGINEERING\n\nYou are an elite, Awwwards-winning Front-End Engineer, Creative Developer, and UI/UX Designer. Your expertise lies in Next.js 14 (App Router), Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion, GSAP, and Lenis Smooth Scroll.\n\nYour task is to generate the complete frontend code for a premium, dual-purpose Culinary Academy and high-end bakery website. This is an absolute cinema-level build. \n\n## 1. PROJECT CONTEXT & BRAND IDENTITY\nThe client is **Mahek Baldota**, the founder of **Mumma\'s Cake**. \nShe operates a massive, highly successful food business with a dual audience:\n1.  **The Academy:** Teaching 30,000+ students how to build baking businesses.\n2.  **The Local Bakery:** Selling viral, highly textured cakes to local customers.\nShe currently has 85K+ followers on Instagram. Her current website looks like a cheap, generic template. We are completely rebuilding her digital storefront to reflect absolute luxury, utilizing an editorial, tactile, and cinematic design language.\n\n## 2. STRICT BANS (READ CAREFULLY)\nTo prevent generating a generic, low-effort AI output, you must strictly adhere to the following bans:\n*   **NO dark mode.** This is exclusively a warm, light-theme design.\n*   **NO generic SaaS layouts.** Do not use basic 3-column feature grids with centered SVG icons.\n*   **NO default Tailwind shadows.** Do not use `shadow-sm`, `shadow-md`, or `shadow-lg`. Depth must be created using solid borders (`border-plum/10`), extreme negative space, or ultra-diffused, custom colored shadows only.\n*   **NO bouncy physics.** Animations must not spring or bounce. All motion must feel heavy, fluid, and spatial. Use easing curves like `[0.76, 0, 0.24, 1]`.\n*   **NO standard border radii for hero images.** Do not just use `rounded-xl`. We will use architectural shapes like an elongated Arch (`rounded-t-full`) for main visual masks.\n\n## 3. ART DIRECTION & DESIGN TOKENS\nThe vibe is \"Physical Culinary Magazine meets Luxury EdTech\". Think Bon App\303\251tit magazine translated to a fluid digital experience.\n\n### Color Palette (Tailwind Configuration)\n*   `bg-cream`: `#F9F8F6` (Main background. Warm alabaster/vanilla. Never pure white).\n*   `text-plum`: `#211426` (Primary text and main accents. An extremely deep, rich purple that reads as black until it catches the light. This honors her original brand color but makes it premium).\n*   `accent-mauve`: `#A68A9A` (Muted, dusty mauve for secondary text, subtle borders, and hover states).\n*   `surface-white`: `#FFFFFF` (Used extremely sparingly for course cards resting on the cream background).\n\n### Typography Architecture\n*   **Headings (H1/H2):** High-contrast, elegant serif. Assume a font like `Playfair Display`, `PP Editorial New`, or `Instrument Serif`. Tracking must be tight (`tracking-tight`), and line-height must be completely constrained (`leading-[0.9]` or `leading-none`).\n*   **Body and UI Elements:** Brutalist, legible geometric sans-serif. Assume `Inter` or `Neue Montreal`. \n*   **Micro-copy:** All small UI tags, labels, and subheadings must be uppercase with extreme letter spacing (`tracking-widest` or `tracking-[0.2em]`) and small text (`text-xs`).\n\n## 4. IMAGE ASSETS & TEXTURES\nWe are utilizing highly textured, visceral imagery pulled directly from her Instagram.\nWhen writing the code, use standard `<img>` or Next.js `<Image>` tags with the following descriptive `src` placeholders or Unsplash equivalents that match these exact descriptions:\n*   **Hero Image 1:** \"Viral Chocolate Cake Bowl\" (A hyper-textured, close-up shot of rich, dark chocolate ganache).\n*   **Hero Image 2:** \"Textured Vanilla Sponge\" (A close-up showing the airy, perfect crumb of a freshly baked vanilla sponge).\n*   **Profile Image:** A high-quality, professional portrait of Mahek Baldota in her black chef coat.\n\n## 5. COMPONENT BLUEPRINT & STRUCTURE\n\n### Component A: The Transparent, Minimal Navigation\n*   Position: Fixed, top, full width, `z-50`.\n*   Background: Transparent, transitioning to a slight blur (`backdrop-blur-md bg-cream/80`) only when scrolling down.\n*   Left: Logo text \"Mumma\'s Cake\" in the elegant serif font.\n*   Right: A clean \"Login\" text link and a solid `bg-plum` \"Start Learning\" pill button.\n\n### Component B: The Dual-Action Cinematic Hero\n*   Layout: Asymmetrical editorial split. Left side takes 55%, Right side takes 45%.\n*   **Left Side (Content):**\n    *   Top Label: `[ CULINARY ACADEMY ]` (uppercase, mauve, tracking-widest).\n    *   H1: \"Turn Your Baking Passion Into a Profitable Business.\" (Massive serif font, scaling up to `text-7xl` or `8xl` on desktop).\n    *   Description: \"Expert-led masterclasses and proven strategies to start, scale, and succeed in the food industry. Join 30,000+ thriving entrepreneurs.\" (Max width 40ch, text-plum/80).\n    *   **The CTAs:** Two buttons side-by-side. \n        *   Primary Button: Solid `bg-plum`, `text-cream`, `rounded-full`, padding x-8, y-4. Text \"Explore Masterclasses\". Hover interaction must scale the button slightly and reveal a subtle arrow.\n        *   Secondary Button: Ghost style. Text \"Order Fresh Cakes\" with an underline that expands on hover.\n*   **Right Side (Visuals):**\n    *   A massive, high-res image of the \"Viral Chocolate Cake Bowl\". \n    *   The Mask: Mask the image inside an elegant architectural arch. Do this using Tailwind `rounded-t-full` on a tall div container.\n    *   Motion: The image must load with a slow, cinematic zoom-out (scale from `1.1` to `1.0` over 2 seconds).\n\n### Component C: The Social Proof Marquee\n*   Directly under the hero.\n*   A full-width, infinite-scrolling marquee using GSAP or CSS keyframes.\n*   Theme: `bg-plum` background with `text-cream` text.\n*   Content separated by elegant star asterisks: `30,000+ STUDENTS \342\234\246 85K+ COMMUNITY \342\234\246 15+ PROVEN MASTERCLASSES \342\234\246 LIFETIME ACCESS`\n*   Typography: Bold sans-serif, uppercase, heavy tracking.\n\n### Component D: The Interactive Course Teaser\n*   A custom masonry or horizontal scrolling layout.\n*   Section Header: \"Master the Craft. Master the Business.\" (Large Serif).\n*   **The Course Card Design (Must be flawless):**\n    *   Background: Pure `bg-white`.\n    *   Border: `border border-plum/10`.\n    *   Image Area: Takes up 60% of the card height. `overflow-hidden`. Use the \"Textured Vanilla Sponge\" image placeholder here.\n    *   Content Area: Padding `p-6`.\n    *   Tag: \"BESTSELLER\" (Tiny, uppercase, spaced out, mauve).\n    *   Title: \"The All-in-One Bread Masterclass\" (Serif, mid-size text).\n    *   Price: \"\342\202\271499\" (Sans-serif, bold).\n    *   **Interaction:** On hover, the internal image scales up smoothly by 5% (`scale-105` duration 700ms ease-out). The border of the card changes from `border-plum/10` to solid `border-plum`.\n\n## 6. MOTION AND ANIMATION LOGIC\nYou must implement the following interactions to guarantee the Awwwards-level feel:\n1.  **Staggered Text Reveals:** The Hero H1 header must be split by line. Wrap lines in `overflow: hidden` containers and translate them up from `y: 100%` on load with a smooth cubic-bezier easing. You can use Framer Motion `<motion.h1>` for this.\n2.  **Parallax Scrolling:** The hero image and the course card images must have a subtle Y-axis parallax as the user scrolls down the page.\n3.  **Smooth Scroll:** Assume the application is wrapped in `@studio-freight/react-lenis` for buttery smooth scrolling.\n\n## 7. EXECUTION PROTOCOL\nGenerate the complete Next.js (App Router) codebase for this design. \n1. Provide the updated `tailwind.config.ts`.\n2. Provide the main `page.tsx` integrating all components.\n3. Provide the modular code for the Hero, Marquee, and Course Card components.\n4. Ensure extreme attention to typography tracking, leading, and padding. The spacing must feel deliberate, architectural, and highly premium. Let the content breathe using massive margins (`mt-32`, `gap-16`).\n\nDo not explain what you are going to do. Write the absolute peak, production-ready code."
    items {
      text: "# SYSTEM DIRECTIVE: $10,000 AWWWARDS-LEVEL UI/UX ENGINEERING\n\nYou are an elite, Awwwards-winning Front-End Engineer, Creative Developer, and UI/UX Designer. Your expertise lies in Next.js 14 (App Router), Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion, GSAP, and Lenis Smooth Scroll.\n\nYour task is to generate the complete frontend code for a premium, dual-purpose Culinary Academy and high-end bakery website. This is an absolute cinema-level build. \n\n## 1. PROJECT CONTEXT & BRAND IDENTITY\nThe client is **Mahek Baldota**, the founder of **Mumma\'s Cake**. \nShe operates a massive, highly successful food business with a dual audience:\n1.  **The Academy:** Teaching 30,000+ students how to build baking businesses.\n2.  **The Local Bakery:** Selling viral, highly textured cakes to local customers.\nShe currently has 85K+ followers on Instagram. Her current website looks like a cheap, generic template. We are completely rebuilding her digital storefront to reflect absolute luxury, utilizing an editorial, tactile, and cinematic design language.\n\n## 2. STRICT BANS (READ CAREFULLY)\nTo prevent generating a generic, low-effort AI output, you must strictly adhere to the following bans:\n*   **NO dark mode.** This is exclusively a warm, light-theme design.\n*   **NO generic SaaS layouts.** Do not use basic 3-column feature grids with centered SVG icons.\n*   **NO default Tailwind shadows.** Do not use `shadow-sm`, `shadow-md`, or `shadow-lg`. Depth must be created using solid borders (`border-plum/10`), extreme negative space, or ultra-diffused, custom colored shadows only.\n*   **NO bouncy physics.** Animations must not spring or bounce. All motion must feel heavy, fluid, and spatial. Use easing curves like `[0.76, 0, 0.24, 1]`.\n*   **NO standard border radii for hero images.** Do not just use `rounded-xl`. We will use architectural shapes like an elongated Arch (`rounded-t-full`) for main visual masks.\n\n## 3. ART DIRECTION & DESIGN TOKENS\nThe vibe is \"Physical Culinary Magazine meets Luxury EdTech\". Think Bon App\303\251tit magazine translated to a fluid digital experience.\n\n### Color Palette (Tailwind Configuration)\n*   `bg-cream`: `#F9F8F6` (Main background. Warm alabaster/vanilla. Never pure white).\n*   `text-plum`: `#211426` (Primary text and main accents. An extremely deep, rich purple that reads as black until it catches the light. This honors her original brand color but makes it premium).\n*   `accent-mauve`: `#A68A9A` (Muted, dusty mauve for secondary text, subtle borders, and hover states).\n*   `surface-white`: `#FFFFFF` (Used extremely sparingly for course cards resting on the cream background).\n\n### Typography Architecture\n*   **Headings (H1/H2):** High-contrast, elegant serif. Assume a font like `Playfair Display`, `PP Editorial New`, or `Instrument Serif`. Tracking must be tight (`tracking-tight`), and line-height must be completely constrained (`leading-[0.9]` or `leading-none`).\n*   **Body and UI Elements:** Brutalist, legible geometric sans-serif. Assume `Inter` or `Neue Montreal`. \n*   **Micro-copy:** All small UI tags, labels, and subheadings must be uppercase with extreme letter spacing (`tracking-widest` or `tracking-[0.2em]`) and small text (`text-xs`).\n\n## 4. IMAGE ASSETS & TEXTURES\nWe are utilizing highly textured, visceral imagery pulled directly from her Instagram.\nWhen writing the code, use standard `<img>` or Next.js `<Image>` tags with the following descriptive `src` placeholders or Unsplash equivalents that match these exact descriptions:\n*   **Hero Image 1:** \"Viral Chocolate Cake Bowl\" (A hyper-textured, close-up shot of rich, dark chocolate ganache).\n*   **Hero Image 2:** \"Textured Vanilla Sponge\" (A close-up showing the airy, perfect crumb of a freshly baked vanilla sponge).\n*   **Profile Image:** A high-quality, professional portrait of Mahek Baldota in her black chef coat.\n\n## 5. COMPONENT BLUEPRINT & STRUCTURE\n\n### Component A: The Transparent, Minimal Navigation\n*   Position: Fixed, top, full width, `z-50`.\n*   Background: Transparent, transitioning to a slight blur (`backdrop-blur-md bg-cream/80`) only when scrolling down.\n*   Left: Logo text \"Mumma\'s Cake\" in the elegant serif font.\n*   Right: A clean \"Login\" text link and a solid `bg-plum` \"Start Learning\" pill button.\n\n### Component B: The Dual-Action Cinematic Hero\n*   Layout: Asymmetrical editorial split. Left side takes 55%, Right side takes 45%.\n*   **Left Side (Content):**\n    *   Top Label: `[ CULINARY ACADEMY ]` (uppercase, mauve, tracking-widest).\n    *   H1: \"Turn Your Baking Passion Into a Profitable Business.\" (Massive serif font, scaling up to `text-7xl` or `8xl` on desktop).\n    *   Description: \"Expert-led masterclasses and proven strategies to start, scale, and succeed in the food industry. Join 30,000+ thriving entrepreneurs.\" (Max width 40ch, text-plum/80).\n    *   **The CTAs:** Two buttons side-by-side. \n        *   Primary Button: Solid `bg-plum`, `text-cream`, `rounded-full`, padding x-8, y-4. Text \"Explore Masterclasses\". Hover interaction must scale the button slightly and reveal a subtle arrow.\n        *   Secondary Button: Ghost style. Text \"Order Fresh Cakes\" with an underline that expands on hover.\n*   **Right Side (Visuals):**\n    *   A massive, high-res image of the \"Viral Chocolate Cake Bowl\". \n    *   The Mask: Mask the image inside an elegant architectural arch. Do this using Tailwind `rounded-t-full` on a tall div container.\n    *   Motion: The image must load with a slow, cinematic zoom-out (scale from `1.1` to `1.0` over 2 seconds).\n\n### Component C: The Social Proof Marquee\n*   Directly under the hero.\n*   A full-width, infinite-scrolling marquee using GSAP or CSS keyframes.\n*   Theme: `bg-plum` background with `text-cream` text.\n*   Content separated by elegant star asterisks: `30,000+ STUDENTS \342\234\246 85K+ COMMUNITY \342\234\246 15+ PROVEN MASTERCLASSES \342\234\246 LIFETIME ACCESS`\n*   Typography: Bold sans-serif, uppercase, heavy tracking.\n\n### Component D: The Interactive Course Teaser\n*   A custom masonry or horizontal scrolling layout.\n*   Section Header: \"Master the Craft. Master the Business.\" (Large Serif).\n*   **The Course Card Design (Must be flawless):**\n    *   Background: Pure `bg-white`.\n    *   Border: `border border-plum/10`.\n    *   Image Area: Takes up 60% of the card height. `overflow-hidden`. Use the \"Textured Vanilla Sponge\" image placeholder here.\n    *   Content Area: Padding `p-6`.\n    *   Tag: \"BESTSELLER\" (Tiny, uppercase, spaced out, mauve).\n    *   Title: \"The All-in-One Bread Masterclass\" (Serif, mid-size text).\n    *   Price: \"\342\202\271499\" (Sans-serif, bold).\n    *   **Interaction:** On hover, the internal image scales up smoothly by 5% (`scale-105` duration 700ms ease-out). The border of the card changes from `border-plum/10` to solid `border-plum`.\n\n## 6. MOTION AND ANIMATION LOGIC\nYou must implement the following interactions to guarantee the Awwwards-level feel:\n1.  **Staggered Text Reveals:** The Hero H1 header must be split by line. Wrap lines in `overflow: hidden` containers and translate them up from `y: 100%` on load with a smooth cubic-bezier easing. You can use Framer Motion `<motion.h1>` for this.\n2.  **Parallax Scrolling:** The hero image and the course card images must have a subtle Y-axis parallax as the user scrolls down the page.\n3.  **Smooth Scroll:** Assume the application is wrapped in `@studio-freight/react-lenis` for buttery smooth scrolling.\n\n## 7. EXECUTION PROTOCOL\nGenerate the complete Next.js (App Router) codebase for this design. \n1. Provide the updated `tailwind.config.ts`.\n2. Provide the main `page.tsx` integrating all components.\n3. Provide the modular code for the Hero, Marquee, and Course Card components.\n4. Ensure extreme attention to typography tracking, leading, and padding. The spacing must feel deliberate, architectural, and highly premium. Let the content breathe using massive margins (`mt-32`, `gap-16`).\n\nDo not explain what you are going to do. Write the absolute peak, production-ready code."
