    web_documents {
      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE61NecRcgwjY4mtmotcTYzezZh-W0F_YQB66FMyh5-HnWgZNONR5EYaWy8-dOYHY6MWU-nljzIAic9oizvDvCFBmB4zOf5voZt7FdMv3NO_NMBXWeSGZkQAZ60Ly8kS8AHv9bzA_ZY8pTr5JY1z2l7nzAJoheZ1Yycs_UgyBI0s6loSJI="
      title: "dev.to"
    }
    summary: "The error `Uncaught TypeError: Cannot set property fetch of #<Window> which has only a getter` indicates an attempt to reassign the `fetch` property on the global `Window` object, which is not permitted because `window.fetch` is a read-only property in web browsers[1].\n\nThis `TypeError` typically arises in strict mode JavaScript (which is the default for modules and classes) when code tries to directly overwrite the native `fetch` function. In non-strict mode, such an assignment might be silently ignored, but in strict mode, it throws an error[1].\n\nCommon scenarios that can lead to this error include:\n*   **Direct Overriding of `window.fetch`**: Code attempting to replace the native `fetch` API, perhaps for polyfilling, testing, or custom request interception, might incorrectly try to assign a new function directly to `window.fetch`[2][3].\n*   **Third-Party Libraries or Polyfills**: Certain older libraries or specific versions of tools might try to modify `window.fetch` in an unsupported way. For instance, discussions mention issues with `Realm` SDK versions or how `raven-js` might interact with `window.fetch`[4][5].\n*   **Bundling or Transpilation Issues**: In some cases, how JavaScript modules are bundled or transpiled can lead to code that inadvertently tries to overwrite global browser APIs[6].\n\nTo properly modify or intercept `fetch` requests, a common approach is to use a `Proxy` object. A `Proxy` allows you to intercept fundamental operations, such as calling a function, and can be used to add hooks or custom logic to `fetch` requests without directly reassigning the `window.fetch` property[7].\n\nSources:\n[1] [mozilla.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGWUa0U-drcaX8UsXIVgClgVN0vCscsWVvJSttjmp_mBZHAKORJpKSvT-0MYAMcx4jq4JjbEM4yomEcKSqWjyg6iSifKZhHnxw0qAd39ZGRm17ZgyRipASYWXGGFqyAbDXej6U_i8x4inlzqgMLLNASvGlsbur90c56Cz14ChqiULX7Bd5PldgD72dgngOW)\n[2] [stackoverflow.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHXZnKo_EN6h33Ji_5iurVU29pxJssWVdwEj8FyLXU5PcainCowy2MszSDuajJxkBJNucOKxGnIO5lPWY5soIeMBF2zg_gHswCsnc5Ohz_ITCAKWeeuHgqBWM3OqPzPqDc06NchrNMhaXn2uZtW3COIBpumv3TVfZWUOLuaCMmuS4hokEZkiTI0Cjk8gnaZG0D-G-pxJpZjTLJCsONRE7OePIE4drCiIclGkWqR451Cxdbkv4pyKL0=)\n[3] [medium.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHq77tk1orgG4K48PRc2tobrBb5N7HvFFZAc1UhaUxdbf9biWPxKwjLq3Xofr2wbIqZ7ITJoD-4hpuZkNe2NShPJMpJ9GEpafOr8WnTUs_RINxBWhV6SeBKgKukgdUiIbclWVAnTOYwr0UqWYTCAJaO7nyGG41FcjIw-4VCRiiYQRLc2-S98_Ie0zjFGvg=)\n[4] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHEeZeCwKJ2GYhGL-LJLZENc-9HUISLZ22VaKm6bsDhJqJpG-JVhlz8zgpud8yrtrRZXPjC9M61msve-LZRDAdFj2Nt0XvzxNGi13AB6e5pemPPpignFuPS8mk4UXWb0Veq4PliuYa6)\n[5] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG_AIzoGUwUnvn5MDOZiupKzXagpDNqWA9fmOrpclheAX22_nZ6UPFEcPfEGVbq57Zqt8k1NExt1jrI3xhsHOHoWOTEUo8WcKOJvP97vM0bBf9TV9R9IadGyMRaFHRyjWC8gajXPtHJ1xM7aU6YJ70=)\n[6] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE58-sGWBl8Y2wtYiwvsCqAgewFpDAYQqs6jm2Y5NeG6UHtza8JJ1DYoCES9L-D39LNVy1yA2aZsfUFhRoLeEmwOHw4c9V-GdAcvYUQFLC-9UwJrgFeKBs3mX0Tad1hLG5OjGdbag==)\n[7] [dev.to](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE61NecRcgwjY4mtmotcTYzezZh-W0F_YQB66FMyh5-HnWgZNONR5EYaWy8-dOYHY6MWU-nljzIAic9oizvDvCFBmB4zOf5voZt7FdMv3NO_NMBXWeSGZkQAZ60Ly8kS8AHv9bzA_ZY8pTr5JY1z2l7nzAJoheZ1Yycs_UgyBI0s6loSJI=)"
