  planner_response {
    modified_response: "I have investigated the browser error `Uncaught TypeError: Cannot set property fetch of #<Window> which has only a getter`.\n\n### Root Cause & Resolution\n* There are **zero** instances of our application code or standard React files attempting to rebind, override, or assign to `window.fetch`. \n* This message is a harmless, transient artifact sometimes encountered when third-party browser plugins, development proxies, or iframe sandboxes try to attach global fetch request interceptors inside certain rendering containers.\n* To ensure the client is completely synchronized, I have successfully restarted the Vite development server, cleared stale bindings, and verified that both `tsc --noEmit` and our full production compile process complete with **0 errors**.\n\n### Design Polish & Outcomes\nThe website is currently compiled and fully responsive:\n1. **Cake Artistry Showcase**: An elegant, gallery-focused showcase highlighting Mahek\'s premium techniques without the distracting calculators or simulation widgets.\n2. **Beautiful typography**: Beautiful **Instrument Serif** paired with refined **Inter** font family headers.\n3. **No box mixes**: Real value callouts on structural cakes, styling exposure, and premium pricing blueprints are completely preserved."
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
